be nice if we got a lure atol's?&quot; just the week earlier I thought the same, it's true. Here's my list of stuff that I'd liked to have seen in planes of power but didn't make it:<br>
<br>
Lure Based Atol's: with spiraling magic resists, why not?<br>
Magic based POP rain: mages get it, why not us?<br>
Upgrade to our quadspells: A 65 wizard using the 51 pillar as his main source of xp is a bit silly to me- why didn't we get an upgrade?<br>
Big ice nuke: Where is it, eh?<br>
Forward-only shadowstep: a shadowstep that moves you only forward, instead of a random direction. figured it'd be neat<br>
More SCS ranks: its only good!<br>
<br>
some of the stuff I thought was just silly. we're nuke masters, right? I wonder then why druids have a draught based rain- we don't, mages get a pop magic based rain and druid ice nukes are bigger in size than ours! i found it, hm, odd! the druid one also is 26% more fast dmg than our rain(gems recast + cast time). droods are no big nukers but I /boggle when I see thsoe sorts of things! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=antionidesrz@graffeswizardcompilation>AntionidesRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 8:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> A big ice nuke, and a new AE for quadding. Something in the 1.1k range that had a nice low resist check like the draughts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=throes>Throes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Flintnilf the Wise</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 10:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1>     big ice nuke is a necessity. Our ice nukes have gone up a total of 100 dmg since ice comet at level 49. Stop the pain already, we've been asking for it for months. <br>
